2022 was a wonderful year! I went to weddings, birthdays, traveled to the swamps, the desert, performed at The Grand Ole Opry, went to a wnba game, grew okra, went to concerts and museums, stayed in a Rocky themed air bnb, moved into a new recording studio. I loved it all and took a bunch of fun pictures while I’m at it. Let’s hope 2023 is even more magical! Love you!

More 2022! Saw Jurassic Park on a big screen while in a swimming pool, dogs birthday party, 4th of July in Cincinnati, a honkeytonk in Nashville and a lil Grand Ol Opry performance. It feels good to be alive!
Happy 2023!

Raining in Munich 🇩🇪

These are very tame images I took today. There are so much more. You can feel the heartache when you walk inside. There’s an entire community of people outside who at the time had no idea what was going on even a hundred yards away. Someone pointed out that birds do not fly or land here. It’s very dark and upsetting, but important to see so it doesn’t happen again

Last night in Munich…saw Marienplatz (built in 1158, destroyed in ww2 and rebuilt), then one of the most beautiful churches I’ve ever seen…then got a little too tipsy at a local bar by my air bnb. Now on the train again! Journey is nearing an end and I don’t know how to return to real life after this
I am lost!
I’m safe!
This was built in the 1300’s and wasn’t bombed in the war. It burned in 1693 and was rebuilt. You can feel the history here
Built in 1342 and survived the war. I was scared at first but my air bnb is growing on me.
Such a small lovely town ♥️
Breakfast in a home built in 1342 in the Rhine Valley
Waiting for the bus in a sleepy town
I’m so relaxed after the spa and debating on getting a slice of cake (I’m gonna get the cake)

Spa! I think Baden Baden is almost like Monaco but not talked about as much. I was able to get an air bnb about 30 minutes outside the city so it was cheaper, but I can see the quiet luxury everywhere. The spa was as much as a spa in LA, no massages, just pure ground water filtered through marble. The intricacies and artistry were outstanding. I can not express enough how magical this experience is
It’s my last night in this little town. I’ve been resting all day. Everywhere is closed except a restaurant down the street I’ve been going to nightly . I don’t know what to do..,go out or stay in?

Checking out of the old home. I had the best sleep of my life here. Signed the guestbook and had breakfast (soft boiled egg, fresh butter, bread and coffee). Now off to Frankfurt where I fly out tomorrow.
Here’s the history of the place ♥️
Photo dump…I got back yesterday and slept 12 hours. Will probably rest, do laundry and groceries today but I’m so happy I pushed myself to go abroad solo and have the most magical experience 🇩🇪🥰

More!

2023 year in photos..took a solo trip to Germany. Trip of a lifetime! Stayed in a house built in the 1300’s, Munich, Berlin, Baden Baden. Want to go again! Performed at the legendary Balboa Theatre, AND a Murderfist reunion at Dynasty Typewriter. Went to the beach, hiking, live music events, and a horse race? Eventful year, I didn’t include everything I wanted and could make more of these? Hug your friends and family, and take yourself out solo sometime. Let’s make 2024 even better
